# Mini Backend

The smallest possible backend — two JSON endpoints.

## Run it

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

Server starts at `http://127.0.0.1:8000`

## Test it

**In your browser**, visit:
- http://127.0.0.1:8000/
- http://127.0.0.1:8000/status

**With curl:**
```bash
curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/
curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/status
```

## Publish to GitHub

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Minimal FastAPI backend with two JSON endpoints"
gh repo create mini-backend --public --source=. --push
```

(If you don't have the `gh` CLI, create an empty repo on github.com instead, then run:)
```bash
git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/mini-backend.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```
